# HTTP response headers for static hosts that honour a `_headers` file
# (Cloudflare Pages, Netlify). The full Content-Security-Policy (with per-script
# hashes) is emitted per-page as a <meta> tag by Astro's CSP feature — but a
# <meta> CSP MUST ignore `frame-ancestors`, so we ALSO send it as a real header
# here. This header carries ONLY `frame-ancestors` so it can't conflict with the
# meta policy's script/style hashing; the rest is the meta CSP + the transport/UA
# hardening headers below.

/*
  Content-Security-Policy: frame-ancestors 'none'
  Strict-Transport-Security: max-age=63072000; includeSubDomains; preload
  X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff
  X-Frame-Options: DENY
  Referrer-Policy: no-referrer
  Cross-Origin-Opener-Policy: same-origin
  Cross-Origin-Resource-Policy: same-origin
  Permissions-Policy: accelerometer=(), browsing-topics=(), camera=(), geolocation=(), gyroscope=(), magnetometer=(), microphone=(), payment=(), usb=()
  X-Permitted-Cross-Domain-Policies: none

# Long-cache immutable build assets.
/_astro/*
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=31536000, immutable
